than journal articles¹. Code, data, results, or tools of previous finished or
Reusing research objects allows for reproduction, verification, building up
upon and extending existing work, evidence synthesis, and minimizing
duplicate efforts². The more reusable the different research outputs are
at any stage of your project, the better.
The FAIR principles³ center around richly curated metadata to reach maximal reusability.
In practice, creating fully FAIR resources is difficult in systems that yet lack or fail to
incentivize the necessary standards and procedures. But reusability should be improved
We introduce four widely accessible strategies that can elevate reusability as a byproduct
of pragmatic research data management, even when compliance to FAIR isn't yet

text.tspan: Can you answer the following questions about your research output?

tspan.tspan: Can you and others identify each element of
Which version of your script was used to generate the output?
What is the precise software environment your analysis was run in?
Exactly what data, in which version, has been used?
Can your project speak for itself?
Is the parametrization of your analysis “codified” and simply structured?
Is relevant processing metadata (e.g. configuration, parametrization)
machine-readable, and is it picked up automatically by the tools that use it?
Has relevant process metadata been validated via direct use?
Can you and others infer what has been done to obtain a result?
Are your project's components transparent, and
Can someone unfamiliar with your project infer all relevant elements just
based on the structure of your project?
Is everything that can be reused in a different context a stand-alone entity?
Does your project declare dependencies to all relevant elements of the
Is your project ready to move?
Does your project contain all relevant elements for successful execution
Do your scripts reference project elements with only relative paths?
Can you move your project to a different computer, or from local to cloud
infrastructure, and execute it without adjustments?
